OL,3,CShould you switch or fix? Energy bills
OL,4,Cto rise from October
OL,6,FGas and electricity prices will rise
OL,7,Ffrom October after the energy
OL,8,Fregulator raised its price cap by 2%,
OL,9,Fputting a further squeeze on
OL,10,Fhouseholds this winter.
OL,12,FThe increase, which exceeded the
OL,13,Fexpected rise, means a household using
OL,14,Fa typical amount of energy will pay
OL,15,F#1,755 a year, up #2.93 a month or #35
OL,16,Fa year on the current cap.
OL,18,FITV News explains how you can save on
OL,19,Fyour energy bills and what help is out
OL,20,Fthere for those struggling.
