OL,3,CShould you switch or fix? Energy bills
OL,4,Cto rise from October
OL,6,FOfgem's figures indicate what a
OL,7,Fhousehold using gas and electricity,
OL,8,Fand paying by direct debit, can expect
OL,9,Fto pay if their energy consumption is
OL,10,Ftypical.
OL,12,FBut remember, it's the rates that are
OL,13,Fcapped, not a household's total bills.
OL,14,FPeople still pay for the amount of
OL,15,Fenergy they use - so if it is above
OL,16,Fthe average, they will pay more, and
OL,17,Fif it is below, they will pay less.
OL,19,FThe price cap is set every three
OL,20,Fmonths and is now set to rise slightly
OL,21,Ffrom October 1.
