OL,3,CShould you switch or fix? Energy bills
OL,4,Cto rise from October
OL,6,FIt is usually largely driven up or
OL,7,Fdown based on the wholesale costs of
OL,8,Fenergy, but it is different this time.
OL,10,FOfgem says this price cap increase is
OL,11,Fdriven by an increase in electricity
OL,12,F"balancing costs" ` incurred by
OL,13,Fnetwork operators to ensure a stable
OL,14,Felectricity supply, for when there is
OL,15,Fboth too much power and too little
OL,16,Fpower in the system, with the level
OL,17,Fset by the National Electricity System
OL,18,FOperator. This is adding around #1.23
OL,19,Fa month to the average household bill.
