OL,3,CShould you switch or fix? Energy bills
OL,4,Cto rise from October
OL,6,FMartin Lewis, founder of Money Saving
OL,7,FExpert, urged people to "ditch the cap
OL,8,Fif you can". He says now is a good
OL,9,Ftime for people to take stock of their
OL,10,Ffinances and shop around for a cheaper
OL,11,Fdeal.
OL,13,FIn a post on X, he wrote: "Now we know
OL,14,Fthe Cap will be at the current rate or
OL,15,Fhigher until at least the end of the
OL,16,Fyear, it's easy to compare to the
OL,17,Fcheapest fixes... they are on average
OL,18,Fnearly 17% less than the Oct Cap rate
OL,19,F(c#250/yr cheaper on a typical bill)
OL,20,Fand have guaranteed rates, so you know
OL,21,Fthey won't rise for at least a year."
