OL,3,CShould you switch or fix? Energy bills
OL,4,Cto rise from October
OL,6,FEven Ofgem itself has now advised
OL,7,Fcustomers to start looking for a
OL,8,Fbetter deal.
OL,10,FTim Jarvis, the regulator's director
OL,11,Fgeneral of markets, said: "While
OL,12,Ftoday's change is below inflation, we
OL,13,Fknow customers might not be feeling it
OL,14,Fin their pockets.
OL,16,F"There are things you can do though `
OL,17,Fconsider a fixed tariff as this could
OL,18,Fsave more than #200 against the new
OL,19,Fcap. Paying by direct debit or smart
OL,20,Fpay as you go could also save you
OL,21,Fmoney."
